Citations
Date: 0/0/2004
Source: Hooked
Author: JOHNSON
Vol / Page: 205
Edition:
Quote: When it was time to pay the fees for [Chatham Islands] children who went to the mainland for secondary school, it was time to pick some paua. It was hardly necessary to get wet feet. Lifting them out of the rock pools was called 'paua bending'.
